rComments: Khalid was my favourite teacher at the UofT. The most caring and thoughtful Prof you can have. He inspires you to learn more about political development and changes your viewpoint on global affairs. I think the critical perspective that he teaches should be the standard in every University class. Wish there were more people like him, role model.

He is one of my favorite prof in u of t. His provided materials are difficult make sure you read and prepare for the class! But he always gives complicated materials a good explanation and make your life easier! I've learned a lot from his class.

Khalid is one of the best professors I've ever had at U of T. He introduced a lot of concepts that isn't taught in mainstream political science. Get ready ready, participate, and engage the material---Khalid will make sure of that. If you visit him during if office hours, he's more than happy to help, and he truly cares about his students!

The course had a clear structure in the reading and assignment element but class time is all discussion based and not that well organized. The readings were easy as were the assignments  but it requires a bit of more effort than usual. The prof creates an awesome environment.

rComments: The course for those who are interested in the subject  of negotiating peace in Africa the course is not that difficult. The professor is clear as is the structure of the course. Its highly discussion based and even for those who dont participate he makes a very friendly environment. The assignments are easy until the essay.
